Troubleshooting Common Issues
Issue 1: Permission Denied Errors
If you encounter permission denied errors during backup or restoration:

# Check file permissions
ls -la /home/$USER/important_data/

# Fix permissions if needed
chmod -R u+rw /home/$USER/important_data/

# Use sudo for system-wide backups (if needed)
sudo rsync -av /etc/ /home/$USER/backups/etc_backup/
Issue 2: Insufficient Disk Space
Monitor disk space during backup operations:

# Check available disk space
df -h

# Check backup directory size
du -sh /home/$USER/backups/

# Clean up old backups if needed
find /home/$USER/backups/ -name "*.tar.gz" -mtime +30 -delete
Issue 3: Cron Jobs Not Running
If cron jobs are not executing:

# Check cron service status
systemctl status cron

# Start cron service if stopped
sudo systemctl start cron

# Check cron logs
grep CRON /var/log/syslog | tail -20

# Verify crontab syntax
crontab -l
Issue 4: Backup Corruption
To handle backup corruption:

# Create checksums for backup verification
find /home/$USER/backups/system_backup -type f -exec md5sum {} \; > /home/$USER/backups/backup_checksums.md5

# Verify backup integrity
cd /home/$USER/backups && md5sum -c backup_checksums.md5
